Serbia: King Konstantin Bodin's relative Stefan Nemanja Vojislavljević is born in Ribnica, Duklja. Exiled by his fathers opponents he settles in Ras, Raška. He is the founder of the most powerful royal house of Medieval Serbia: the Nemanjić dynasty. The dynasty will have a decisive role in shaping and reaffirming the national identity of the Serbs tying it closely to the Byzantine civilizational model.
Russia: Sviatopolk died. He was succeeded by Vsevolod's son, his cousin, Vladimir II Monomakh.
Estonia: Prince Mstislav of Kiev wins a battle against the Chuds (Estonians or people related to Estonians).
Cambodia: Dharanidravarman died, possibly murdered by his great nephew Suryavarman II who succeeded him.
Burma: Myazedi inscription, earliest evidence of a more settled Burmese script
